CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1952, pg. 10 reads: "Holds Annual Program - Sunday, May 11, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority held its annual Job Opportunities Program at the Centre Avenue YWCA for high school girls. Program participants were Sorors Janet Makel, mistress of ceremonies; Janet McClain, Shadie Crosland and Katherine Watson.  Soror Marie Henderson was chairman of the affair.  Taking part on the program following were the above students.  Left to right: Blanche Baker, Judy DeHonney, Gwendolyn Poinsette, Patricia Lightfoot, Lynette May (peeping in), Florence May (seated), president of Alpha Epsilon Chapter. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of students Blanche Baker, Judy DeHonney, Gwendolyn Poinsette, Patricia Lightfoot, Lynette May, gathered across from Florence May, seated at desk, for annual Job Opportunities Program sponsored by Delta Sigma Theta, Centre Avenue YMCA, another pose
